{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"17fbb4ce-e5c4-4336-a2f7-cdf739095806","content":"","toolRequests":[{"toolCallId":"tooluse_nXcTEPxnbZ8lu3Ft0QzjGc","name":"report_intent","arguments":{"intent":"Providing K8s crash dump config"},"type":"function"}],"interactionId":"9c39d2f8-45fa-4587-8683-513471bed88c","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user wants to configure automatic crash dump collection for a NativeAOT .NET 11 app running in Kubernetes. They have `createdump` at `/opt/tools/createdump`. Let me provide the necessary configuration.\n\nFor .NET NativeAOT crash dump collection, there are specific environment variables needed:\n\n1. `DOTNET_DbgEnableMiniDump=1` - Enable mini dump on crash\n2. `DOTNET_DbgMiniDumpType=4` - Full dump (MiniDumpWithFullMemory). Values: 1=Normal, 2=WithPrivateReadWriteMemory, 3=FilterTriage, 4=Full\n\n\n3. `DOTNET_DbgMiniDumpName` - Path/pattern for the dump file\n4. `DOTNET_CreateDumpDiagnostics=1` - Optional, for diagnostics\n5. For NativeAOT specifically, I need to set `DOTNET_DbgCreatedumpPath` to point to the createdump binary since the runtime is compiled into the app itself, which changes how the crash dump mechanism operates.\n\nFor the environment variables, I'm setting `DOTNET_DbgEnableMiniDump=1` to enable dumps, configuring the dump path and type, and pointing to the createdump tool location. In Kubernetes, I'd need to provision a volume for storing the dumps and apply these environment variables to the container spec.","outputTokens":539,"requestId":"CB0B:5DA14:1F9BA58:22DDE30:6A052983"},"id":"b1c9d48a-d861-4c96-8d32-e6720521d4a0","timestamp":"2026-05-14T01:46:54.821Z","parentId":"12d31716-dff4-4f78-b25f-351c75ee57fb"}
